<br>
Should these shields be implemented as they are now on test, even if they allow warriors to gain and maintain agro consistently and hold it against other melee classes bashing or swinging away on the other side of the mob, there is still one hell of a problem. Let's skip the fact that it's a lame fix for an inherrent problem with the class and look at it from a purely game mechanics standpoint.<br>
<br>
If we take the 6-8 second refresh mentioned earlier, which sounds about right to me, and i put the one and only sheild I have...some bone looking thing I got in hate 10 levels ago because noone else wanted it...I will max out my bash skill, at the rate I play, about year 2004, if I have dex buffs at all times. The only time I'm going to use this skill is if i'm the MT on a raid. In xp groups, dps is king and I'm going to be using 2 weapons. If i'm not the MT on a raid, why the hell would I want to cripple my dps by using a shield? So at the rate I raid, maybe 2 to 3 times a week, when I'm the MT maybe 1/3 of the time...that means I should gain maybe 2 to 3 pts in the skill on every raid if I'm lucky. I won't have been using the skill for half or more of my levels like alot of knights do...and I won't have the nasty damage 1h weapons knights now have available, nor can I equip a 2h weapon with a shield, so my skill is going to raise very very slowly because I won't use a shield if I'm not the MT...it would be a bad idea tactically.<br>
<br>
This means that the agro a bash is likely to give you isn't going to happen as i'm going to miss nearly all the time for quite some time. I won't be blocking a whole helluva lot either for the same reason. So tell me again...how does this shield benefit me as a warrior?<br>
