<br>
Meanwhile, the Knights are all outfitted with shields, because some very nice ones drop for them.  Yes, they have probably been mostly banked until now, but if this change goes in, they will come out of the bank.  So the Knights will be kitted and ready to go.<br>
<br>
And, even if these shields give us huge agro from bashing, better than many off hand weapons, won't the Knights have exactly the same agro generation from using their shields?  This means that the Knights will be getting off hand agro, which they never got before, in addition to the agro they already generate casting.  This means HUGE agro for Knights.  Not just better than a Warrior's but whole worlds of better.<br>
<br>
Finally, on top of what I have already outlined, you have to look at the 1hs weapons.  Warrior 1hs weapons were designed with duel wield in mind.  While Knight 1hs weapons were designed with being able to use only one weapon in mind.  Therefore Knight only 1hs weapons consistantly have better damage ratios than Warrior 1hs weapons, its in the game design.  Which means that on top of generating new agro with bash, they will be doing more damage with their primary hand than a Warrior will, which means more agro.<br>
<br>
Let me summerize this so you can understand.<br>
<br>
1.  Knights already cast on mobs, generating more agro than Warriors.<br>
<br>
2.  Shields will give Knights additional off hand agro they never had before, major increase for Knights. If they make the off hand agro of a shield as good or better than most off hand weapons Warriors are using, how do they not give the same benefit to Knights, who don't need it? <br>
<br>
3.  Knights 1hs weapons will still do more damage than Warrior 1hs weapons, generating more agro (barring procs).<br>
<br>
Knights don't NEED an increase in agro control.  Warriors do.  Yet here we have a fix that appears to substantially improve Knight agro control while perhaps only enhancing Warrior agro control slightly.  We have to sacrifice an off hand weapon that was ALREADY generating agro to use a shield that will generate agro.  While Knights don't give up anything they had before, except 2hs damage, which both classes give up when MTing.<br>
<br>
Got it?  If not, please give me your address so I can send you a dollar to buy a clue. <br>
